{
  "lessonId": "p1-m1-w1-l1",
  "title": "The 14 Vowels of Sanskrit",
  "order": 1,
  "estimatedMinutes": 45,
  "objectives": [
    "Learn to recognize all 14 Sanskrit vowels in Devanagari script",
    "Understand the difference between short and long vowels",
    "Practice pronunciation with audio examples"
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "introduction",
      "title": "Introduction to Sanskrit Vowels",
      "content": "Sanskrit has 14 primary vowels, organized in pairs of short and long vowels. Unlike English, the length of a vowel is phonemically significant in Sanskrit - changing the length changes the meaning of a word.",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "title": "Short Vowels (Hrasva)",
      "content": "The five short vowels form the foundation of Sanskrit pronunciation.",
      "order": 2,
      "items": [
        {
          "devanagari": "अ",
          "iast": "a",
          "ipa": "/ə/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'u' in 'but' or 'a' in 'about'",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/a.mp3",
          "category": "short-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "अग्नि",
              "iast": "agni",
              "meaning": "fire",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/agni.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "इ",
          "iast": "i",
          "ipa": "/i/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'i' in 'bit' or 'pin'",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/i.mp3",
          "category": "short-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "इष्ट",
              "iast": "iṣṭa",
              "meaning": "desired",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/ishta.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "उ",
          "iast": "u",
          "ipa": "/u/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'u' in 'put' or 'pull'",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/u.mp3",
          "category": "short-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "उत्तम",
              "iast": "uttama",
              "meaning": "best",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/uttama.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ऋ",
          "iast": "ṛ",
          "ipa": "/r̩/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'ri' in 'Krishna' (vocalic r)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/ri.mp3",
          "category": "short-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "ऋषि",
              "iast": "ṛṣi",
              "meaning": "sage",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/rishi.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ऌ",
          "iast": "ḷ",
          "ipa": "/l̩/",
          "pronunciation": "Vocalic l (very rare in Sanskrit)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/li.mp3",
          "category": "short-vowel",
          "note": "This vowel is extremely rare and appears in only a few words."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "title": "Long Vowels (Dīrgha)",
      "content": "Each short vowel (except ḷ) has a corresponding long vowel that is held for twice the duration.",
      "order": 3,
      "items": [
        {
          "devanagari": "आ",
          "iast": "ā",
          "ipa": "/ɑː/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'a' in 'father' (held longer)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/aa.mp3",
          "category": "long-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "आत्मा",
              "iast": "ātmā",
              "meaning": "soul, self",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/aatma.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ई",
          "iast": "ī",
          "ipa": "/iː/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'ee' in 'see' (held longer)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/ii.mp3",
          "category": "long-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "नदी",
              "iast": "nadī",
              "meaning": "river",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/nadi.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ऊ",
          "iast": "ū",
          "ipa": "/uː/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'oo' in 'boot' (held longer)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/uu.mp3",
          "category": "long-vowel",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "भूमि",
              "iast": "bhūmi",
              "meaning": "earth, land",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/bhumi.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ॠ",
          "iast": "ṝ",
          "ipa": "/r̩ː/",
          "pronunciation": "Long vocalic r (rare)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/rii.mp3",
          "category": "long-vowel",
          "note": "This vowel is rare in Sanskrit texts."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "title": "Diphthongs (Saṃyukta Svara)",
      "content": "Sanskrit has four diphthongs, which are combinations of vowels pronounced as a single sound.",
      "order": 4,
      "items": [
        {
          "devanagari": "ए",
          "iast": "e",
          "ipa": "/eː/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'ay' in 'say' (always long)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/e.mp3",
          "category": "diphthong",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "देव",
              "iast": "deva",
              "meaning": "god",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/deva.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ऐ",
          "iast": "ai",
          "ipa": "/aːi/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'ai' in 'aisle'",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/ai.mp3",
          "category": "diphthong",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "वैदिक",
              "iast": "vaidika",
              "meaning": "Vedic",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/vaidika.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "ओ",
          "iast": "o",
          "ipa": "/oː/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'o' in 'go' (always long)",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/o.mp3",
          "category": "diphthong",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "योग",
              "iast": "yoga",
              "meaning": "union, yoga",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/yoga.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "devanagari": "औ",
          "iast": "au",
          "ipa": "/aːu/",
          "pronunciation": "Like 'ow' in 'cow'",
          "audioFile": "/audio/phonemes/vowels/au.mp3",
          "category": "diphthong",
          "examples": [
            {
              "word": "पौत्र",
              "iast": "pautra",
              "meaning": "grandson",
              "audioFile": "/audio/words/pautra.mp3"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "practice",
      "title": "Pronunciation Practice",
      "content": "Listen to each vowel and repeat after the audio. Pay attention to the difference between short and long vowels.",
      "order": 5,
      "exerciseId": "p1-m1-w1-e1-vowel-recognition"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "title": "Summary",
      "content": "You've learned all 14 vowels of Sanskrit:\n- 5 short vowels: a, i, u, ṛ, ḷ\n- 4 long vowels: ā, ī, ū, ṝ\n- 4 diphthongs: e, ai, o, au\n\nIn the next lesson, you'll learn how these vowels combine with consonants using vowel marks (mātras).",
      "order": 6
    }
  ],
